Global Scoping
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Guess the Output:
const KEY = 'coding_ninjas';
if (true) {
    const KEY = 'ES6';
}
console.log(KEY);
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Options
This problem has only one correct answer
ES6
coding_ninjas
undefined
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Answer:coding_ninjas
Solution Description
This declaration creates a constant whose scope can be either global or local to the block in which it is declared. 
The scope of the inner KEY is only inside the "if" block. That's why the output is 'coding_ninjas.
